sia-picked-black-sea-naval-fight-losing-ukraine-without-fleet-2023-9%5C%22%3ERussia's%20Black%20Sea%20Fleet%20headquarters%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhuge-crimea-attack-ukraine-pry-black-sea-base-russia-navy-2023-9%5C%22%3ERussian%20navy%20dry%20docks%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Its%20strike%20on%20the%20dry%20docks%20took%20out%20a%20landing%20ship%20and%20a%20Kilo-class%20submarine%20and%20will%20further%20hamstring%20Russian%20naval%20logistics.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20attacks%20were%20not%20Kyiv's%20first%20successes%20against%20Russia's%20navy%2C%20but%20Ukraine%20lacks%20a%20fleet%20%E2%80%94%20it%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thedrive.com%2Fthe-war-zone%2F44563%2Fthe-ukrainian-navys-flagship-appears-to-have-been-scuttled%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Escuttled%20its%20flagship%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20March%202022%20to%20prevent%20its%20capture%20by%20Russia%20%E2%80%94%20and%20has%20relied%20on%20asymmetrical%20warfare%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-picked-black-sea-naval-fight-losing-ukraine-without-fleet-2023-9%5C%22%3Eincluding%20naval%20drones%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20to%20counter%20Russia%20in%20the%20Black%20Sea.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussia's%20Black%20Sea%20Fleet%20hasn't%20been%20defeated%2C%20but%20its%20losses%2C%20including%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussian-ships-head-south-as-flagship-moskva-battles-extensive-fire-2022-4%5C%22%3Ethe%20sinking%20of%20its%20flagship%2C%20the%20Moskva%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20weigh%20more%20heavily%20on%20Russia's%20war%20effort%20because%20of%20a%20deal%20signed%20nearly%20a%20century%20ago%20that%20is%20preventing%20Moscow%20from%20bringing%20more%20ships%20into%20the%20Black%20Sea.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EShips%20bottled%20up%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Russia%20Navy%20Day%20Parade%20Warships%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5ac15eaa25c48d1b008b46bb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22912%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERussian%20warships%20at%20the%20Black%20Sea%20Fleet%20base%20in%20Sevastopol%20in%20July%202010.%3Cp%3EAP%20Photo%2FSergey%20Ponomarev%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESigned%20in%201936%2C%20the%20Montreux%20Convention%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.usni.org%2Fmagazines%2Fproceedings%2F2022%2Fmarch%2Fturkey-montreux-convention-and-russian-navy-transits-turkish%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egoverns%20the%20transit%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20merchant%20vessels%20and%20warships%20through%20the%20Dardanelles%20and%20the%20Bosporus%20Strait%20and%20the%20presence%20of%20warships%20in%20the%20Black%20Sea.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20convention%20distinguishes%20between%20Black%20Sea%20powers%20%E2%80%94%20those%20with%20a%20Black%20Sea%20coastline%20%E2%80%94%20and%20non-Black%20Sea%20powers.%20In%20peacetime%2C%20warships%20belonging%20to%20non-Black%20Sea%20powers%20cannot%20stay%20in%20the%20sea%20for%20more%20than%2021%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20convention%20also%20has%20limits%20for%20the%20combined%20tonnage%20of%20vessels%20from%20non-Black%20Sea%20powers%20that%20can%20be%20in%20the%20sea%20at%20one%20time%2C%20capping%20it%20at%20a%20maximum%20of%2045%2C000%20tons%20with%20no%20more%20than%2030%2C000%20tons%20of%20that%20belonging%20to%20one%20country.%20A%20US%20Navy%20Arleigh%20Burke-class%20destroyer%2C%20several%20of%20which%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-navy-warships-in-black-sea-amid-nato-russia-tensions-2021-11%5C%22%3Ehave%20sailed%20into%20the%20sea%20in%20recent%20years%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20is%20about%209%2C000%20tons.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20convention%20doesn't%20specifically%20rule%20out%20aircraft%20carriers%2C%20a%2015%2C000-ton%20limit%20for%20vessels%20of%20non-Black%20Sea%20powers%20transiting%20the%20straits%20effectively%20prohibits%20them.%20Submarines%20from%20non-Black%20Sea%20powers%20are%20also%20not%20allowed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Russian%20Navy's%20diesel-electric%20Kilo%20class%20submarine%20Rostov-on-Don%20sails%20with%20an%20naval%20ensign%20of%20the%20Russian%20Federation%2C%20also%20known%20in%20Russian%20as%20The%20Andreyevsky%20Flag%20on%20it%20through%20the%20Bosphorus%20Strait%20on%20the%20way%20to%20the%20Black%20Sea%20past%20the%20city%20Istanbul%20as%20Sultanahmet%20mosque%20(L)%20and%20Hagia%20Sophia%20mosque%20(R)%20are%20seen%20in%20the%20backround%20on%20February%2013%2C%202022.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64ad633c8ed31300199e6c72%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222661%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERussian%20Navy%20submarine%20Rostov-on-Don%20sails%20through%20the%20Bosphorus%20to%20the%20Black%20Sea%20on%20February%2013%2C%202022.%3Cp%3EOZAN%20KOSE%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ETurkey%20controls%20the%20straits%20connecting%20the%20sea%20to%20the%20Mediterranean%2C%20and%20all%20foreign%20warships%20have%20to%20notify%20Turkey%20prior%20to%20passage%20%E2%80%94%2015%20days%20ahead%20of%20time%20for%20non-Black%20Sea%20powers%20and%20eight%20days%20for%20Black%20Sea%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20war%2C%20the%20convention%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fweb.archive.org%2Fweb%2F20200319171226%2Fhttps%3A%2F%2Fsam.baskent.edu.tr%2Fbelge%2FMontreux_ENG.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epermits%20Turkey%20to%20limit%20the%20passage%20of%20warships%20to%20the%20Black%20Sea%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20even%20if%20Turkey%20is%20not%20at%20war%20%E2%80%94%20unless%20these%20ships%20are%20returning%20to%20their%20base.%20On%20February%2028%2C%202022%2C%20four%20days%20after%20Russia%20attacked%20Ukraine%2C%20Turkey%20invoked%20that%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20Turkey%20is%20not%20a%20belligerent%20in%20the%20conflict%2C%20it%20has%20the%20authority%20to%20restrict%20the%20passage%20of%20the%20warring%20states'%20warships%20across%20the%20straits.%20If%20the%20warship%20is%20returning%20to%20its%20base%20in%20the%20Black%20Sea%2C%20the%20passage%20is%20not%20closed%2C%26quot%3B%20Turkey's%20foreign%20minister%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.navalnews.com%2Fnaval-news%2F2022%2F02%2Fturkey-closes-the-dardanelles-and-bosphorus-to-warships%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20the%20time.%20%26quot%3BAll%20governments%2C%20riparian%20and%20non-riparian%2C%20were%20warned%20not%20to%20send%20warships%20across%20the%20straits.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnkara's%20invocation%20of%20the%20convention%20is%20seen%20as%20significant%20because%20it%20has%20prevented%20Russia%20from%20bolstering%20its%20Black%20Sea%20Fleet.%20If%20Turkey%20were%20to%20open%20the%20straits%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20first%20thing%20you%20would%20see%20is%20a%20significant%20naval%20reinforcement%20from%20other%20parts%20of%20the%20Russian%20fleet%2C%20and%20that%20isn't%20in%20Ukraine's%20interest%20or%20ours%2C%26quot%3B%20Ben%20Wallace%2C%20then%20Britain's%20defense%20minister%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.iiss.org%2Fglobalassets%2Fmedia-library---content--migration%2Ffiles%2Fshangri-la-dialogue%2F2023%2Ffinal-transcripts%2Fp-2%2Fsecond-plenary-session---qa---as-delivered.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20the%20Shangri-La%20Dialogue%20in%20June.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Smoke%20fire%20oil%20fuel%20tank%20drone%20attack%20Sevastopol%20Crimea%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6463ee7d7224930019f326bd%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221181%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESmoke%20rises%20from%20a%20fuel%20tank%20after%20an%20attack%20in%20Sevastopol%20in%20April.%3Cp%3EREUTERS%2FStringer%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Turkey's%20move%20has%20limited%20Russian%20naval%20movements%2C%20experts%20differ%20on%20its%20overall%20impact%20on%20the%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BInitially%20it%20was%20thought%20that%20it%20was%20a%20big%20deal%20that%20some%20of%20the%20Russian%20warships%20were%20prevented%20from%20entering%20the%20Black%20Sea.%20But%20Russia%20had%20a%20massive%20naval%20presence%20there%20anyway%2C%26quot%3B%20including%20six%20ships%20from%20its%20Baltic%20and%20Northern%20fleets%20that%20entered%20the%20sea%20before%20Turkey%20invoked%20the%20convention%2C%20Volodymyr%20Dubovyk%2C%20a%20professor%20at%20Odessa's%20I.%20Mechnikov%20National%20University%2C%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussia's%20ships%20in%20the%20Black%20Sea%20don't%20give%20it%20a%20%26quot%3Bdecisive%20edge%20over%20Ukraine%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20because%20of%20the%20effectiveness%20of%20Ukraine's%20attacks%2C%20those%20ships%20have%20become%20%26quot%3Bsitting%20ducks%26quot%3B%20that%20have%20%26quot%3Bto%20hide%20away%20from%20the%20Ukrainian%20coast%2C%26quot%3B%20Dubovyk%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussian%20warships%20still%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FThe_Lookout_N%2Fstatus%2F1710616079020482891%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eappear%20to%20be%20stationed%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20Sevastopol%2C%20the%20main%20Russian%20naval%20base%20in%20Crimea%2C%20but%20Ukraine's%20success%20in%20targeting%20that%20base%20and%20Russian%20forces%20nearby%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussian-flagship-moskva-sinking-marks-new-era-of-naval-warfare-2022-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewill%20likely%20have%20a%20lasting%20impact%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20that%20these%20developments%20are%20going%20to%20contribute%20to%20a%20change%20in%20thinking%20about%20the%20role%20of%20naval%20power%2C%26quot%3B%20Dubovyk%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EAllied%20help%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221400%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Turkey%20NATO%20Romania%20navy%20Black%20Sea%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5dd4d158fd9db254a82d0274%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22934%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20Turkish%20navy%20frigate%20alongside%20a%20Romanian%20frigate%20in%20the%20Black%20Sea%20in%20February%202018.%3Cp%3ENATO%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20convention%20also%20allows%20Turkey%20to%20shape%20the%20international%20response%20to%20the%20war%2C%20according%20to%20Iulia-Sabina%20Joja%2C%20the%20director%20of%20the%20Black%20Sea%20program%20at%20the%20Middle%20East%20Institute%2C%20a%20think%20tank%20in%20Washington%20DC.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Montreux%20Convention%20is%20confusing%2C%26quot%3B%20Joja%20told%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BIt%20actually%20states%20that%20when%20Turkey%20is%20not%20a%20belligerent%20but%20feels%20threatened%2C%20then%20it%20can%20act%20as%20if%20it%20were%20a%20belligerent.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20such%20a%20case%2C%20Joja%20said%2C%20the%20decision%20about%20which%20warships%20can%20enter%20the%20Black%20Sea%20is%20entirely%20up%20to%20the%20Turkish%20government%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fweb.archive.org%2Fweb%2F20200319171226%2Fhttps%3A%2F%2Fsam.baskent.edu.tr%2Fbelge%2FMontreux_ENG.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20the%20convention%3C%2Fa%3E.%20(Merchant%20ships%20can%20pass%20through%20the%20straits%20freely%2C%20even%20during%20wartime%2C%20and%20satellite%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.csis.org%2Fanalysis%2Fwolf-ships-clothing-russias-militarization-civilian-vessels-black-sea%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eimagery%20suggests%3C%2Fa%3E%20Russia%20is%20using%20them%20to%20move%20military%20hardware%20through%20the%20sea.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20provision%20could%20allow%20Turkey%20to%20let%20warships%20from%20NATO%20navies%20into%20the%20Black%20Sea%2C%20and%20some%20experts%20have%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fbusiness%2Fenergy%2F2023%2F07%2F25%2Fnato-convoys-can-protect-ukraine-s-grain-harvest-from-putin%2F541a151e-2aa3-11ee-a948-a5b8a9b62d84_story.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eadvocated%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20alliance%20seek%20access%20to%20the%20sea%20to%20escort%20merchant%20vessels%20carrying%20Ukrainian%20grain%2C%20thus%20helping%20circumvent%20Russia's%20blockade.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221492%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Ukraine%20Izmail%20Danube%20river%20grain%20cargo%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65304d98211def8ed838b5c9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221119%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20cargo%20ship%20passes%20a%20beach%20on%20the%20Danube%20River%2C%20which%20is%20being%20used%20for%20Ukrainian%20grain%20shipments%2C%20in%20Izmail%20in%20August.%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20convention%20may%20allow%20such%20an%20action%2C%20going%20through%20with%20it%20would%20be%20politically%20difficult%20for%20NATO%20and%20for%20Ankara.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20two%20unknowns%20here%3A%20whether%20the%20Turkish%20government%20is%20willing%20to%20let%20NATO%20maritime%20defense%20capabilities%20in%20and%20whether%20NATO%20allies%20have%20the%20political%20will%20to%20build%20a%20credible%20deterrence%20and%20defense%20in%20the%20Black%20Sea%20region%2C%26quot%3B%20Joja%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETurkey%20is%20a%20NATO%20member%20but%20maintains%20a%20good%20relationship%20with%20Russia.%20That%20has%20at%20times%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fturkey-russia-s400-too-politically-costly-to-get-rid-of-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efrustrated%20other%20NATO%20members%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20Ankara%20used%20it%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aljazeera.com%2Fnews%2F2023%2F7%2F17%2Frussia-ukraine-black-sea-grain-deal-all-you-need-to-know%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eto%20help%20broker%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%202022%20deal%20allowing%20Ukraine%20to%20ship%20grain%20through%20the%20Black%20Sea.%20(Russia%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.npr.org%2F2023%2F09%2F04%2F1197544117%2Frussia-ukraine-grain-deal-turkey%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewithdrew%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20deal%20in%20July%20and%20imposed%20its%20blockade.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAllowing%20NATO%20warships%20into%20the%20Black%20Sea%20now%20would%20test%20Turkey's%20relations%20with%20Russia%2C%20but%2C%20Joja%20said%2C%20it%20would%20also%20benefit%20the%20alliance%2C%20%26quot%3Bcontribute%20to%20security%20in%20the%20Black%20Sea%20region%2C%20and%20would%20indirectly%20even%20help%20Ukraine%20ship%20grain%20out%20of%20the%20Black%20Sea.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EConstantine%20Atlamazoglou%20works%20on%20transatlantic%20and%20European%20security.%20He%20holds%20a%20master's%20degree%20in%20security%20studies%20and%20European%20affairs%20from%20the%20Fletcher%20School%20of%20Law%20and%20Diplomacy.%20You%20can%20contact%20him%20on%20%3Ca%20data-xid%3D%5C%22fr1659647903195fde%5C%22%20data-ml-dynamic-type%3D%5C%22sl%5C%22%20data-ml%3D%5C%22true%5C%22%20data-skimlinks-tracking%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-analytics-module%3D%5C%22body_link%5C%22%20data-ml-dynamic%3D%5C%22true%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22LinkedIn%5C%22%20data-analytics-product-module%3D%5C%22body_link%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%20data-mrf-link%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fin%2Fconstantine-atlamazoglou%5C%22%20data-orig-url%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fin%2Fconstantine-atlamazoglou%5C%22%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%20noindex%20noopener%20sponsored%5C%22%20data-ml-id%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20data-uri%3