chancellor%20came%20as%20Gaza%20faced%20a%2012th%20straight%20day%20of%20ferocious%20Israeli%20bombardment%20in%20retaliation%20for%20a%20shock%20cross-border%20attack%20launched%20by%20Hamas%20on%20October%207%20that%20killed%20at%20least%201%2C400%20people%2C%20most%20of%20them%20civilians.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENearly%203%2C500%20people%20have%20been%20killed%20in%20Gaza%2C%20which%20is%20nearly%20out%20of%20electricity%2C%20food%2C%20water%20and%20fuel.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EPressure%20has%20mounted%20for%20aid%20to%20be%20allowed%20in%20through%20Egypt's%20Rafah%20crossing%20with%20Gaza%2C%20the%20only%20access%20to%20the%20besieged%20territory%20not%20controlled%20by%20Israel.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EPresident%20Sisi%20said%20Egypt%20%26quot%3Bdid%20not%20close%26quot%3B%20the%20crossing%2C%20but%20that%20%26quot%3Bdevelopments%20on%20the%20ground%20and%20the%20repeated%20bombings%20by%20Israel%20of%20the%20Palestinian%20side%20of%20the%20crossing%20have%20prevented%20its%20operation%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHundreds%20of%20lorries%20carrying%20aid%20have%20been%20waiting%20for%20six%20days%20on%20the%20Egyptian%20side%20of%20the%20crossing%2C%20which%20Israeli%20aircraft%20has%20bombed%20four%20times.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOlaf%20Scholz%20told%20reporters%20Berlin%20and%20Cairo%20%26quot%3Bare%20working%20together%20to%20get%20humanitarian%20access%20to%20the%20Gaza%20Strip%20as%20quickly%20as%20possible.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20two%20men%20also%20warned%20against%20the%20threat%20of%20regional%20spillover%2C%20with%20the%20Egyptian%20president%20calling%20for%20%26quot%3Bimmediate%20international%20intervention%26quot%3B%20to%20put%20a%20stop%20to%20%26quot%3Bdangerous%20military%20escalation%20that%20may%20get%20out%20of%20control%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMr%20Scholz%20reiterated%20that%20Germany%20sought%20to%20avoid%20a%20%26quot%3Bconflagration%20in%20the%20Middle%20East%26quot%3B%20and%20warned%20Hezbollah%20and%20Iran%20%26quot%3Bonce%20again%20not%20to%20intervene%20in%20this%20conflict%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPeace%20could%20'fall%20apart'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EPresident%20Sisi%20said%20he%20could%20%26quot%3Bcall%20on%20the%20Egyptian%20people%20to%20come%20out%20and%20express%20their%20rejection%26quot%3B%20of%20the%20displacement%20of%20Palestinians%20from%20Gaza%2C%20%26quot%3Band%20you%20would%20see%20millions%20of%20Egyptians%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20street%20--%20where%20protests%20have%20been%20banned%20for%20nearly%20a%20decade.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EShortly%20after%2C%20Egyptian%20media%20reported%20that%20thousands%20had%20demonstrated%20nationwide%20in%20solidarity%20with%20Gaza.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ECairo's%20Al%20Azhar%20University%20--%20a%20leading%20institution%20in%20Sunni%20Islam%20--%20issued%20a%20call%20late%20on%20Tuesday%20for%20Muslims%20to%20%26quot%3Binvest%20their%20wealth%20in%20supporting%20Palestine%20and%20its%20oppressed%20people%26quot%3B%2C%20urging%20them%20to%20%26quot%3Breview%20their%20dependence%20on%20the%20arrogant%20West%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%201979%2C%20Egypt%20became%20the%20first%20Arab%20state%20to%20make%20peace%20with%20Israel%20following%20the%20Camp%20David%20accords%20of%20the%20previous%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAlthough%20public%20opposition%20to%20Israel%20remains%20widespread%2C%20both%20countries%20have%20maintained%20security%20collaboration%20and%20steady%20diplomatic%20ties.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThat%20peace%20is%20at%20risk%20of%20disintegrating%2C%20Sisi%20said%2C%20if%20there%20is%20a%20mass%20exodus%20of%20Gazans%20to%20Egypt's%20neighbouring%20Sinai%20Peninsula%20that%20would%20risk%20turning%20it%20into%20%26quot%3Ba%20new%20base%20for%20terrorist%20operations%20against%20Israel%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIsrael%20would%20have%20the%20right%20to%20defend%20itself%20and%20its%20national%20security%2C%20and%20therefore%20direct%20strikes%20on%20Egyptian%20lands%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E