E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20768px)%20100vw%2C%20768px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FLarge-planters_11zon-1697535500.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22768%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20large%20planter%20made%20with%20mosaic%20art.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FLarge-planters_11zon-1697535500.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FLarge-planters_11zon-1697535500-300x224.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FLarge-planters_11zon-1697535500-500x374.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FLarge-planters_11zon-1697535500-150x112.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-332386%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22574%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EA%20large%20planter%20made%20with%20mosaic%20art.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%20%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EEco-friendly%20aspects%20of%20their%20business%3C%2Fh2%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20duo%20is%20very%20particular%20that%20they%20do%20not%20destroy%20anything%20in%20nature.%20They%20do%20not%20support%20cutting%20down%20trees.%C2%A0%20That%E2%80%99s%20why%20they%20use%20discarded%20driftwood%20and%20recycled%20timber%20%E2%80%93%20the%20two%20most%20environmentally-friendly%20ways%20to%20acquire%20wood.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20try%20as%20much%20as%20possible%20to%20salvage%20and%20upcycle%20our%20raw%20materials%2C%E2%80%9D%20explains%20Yohann.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EEvery%20few%20months%20they%20go%20to%20the%20beach%20at%20Gorai%20fishing%20village%20and%20pick%20up%20pieces%20of%20driftwood%20which%20they%20feel%20they%20can%20work%20with%20to%20make%20something%20beautiful.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENaomi%20uses%20scrap%20and%20discarded%20materials%20like%20old%2C%20broken%20tiles%2C%20broken%20bangles%2C%20cracked%20vase%20pieces%2C%20pebbles%20and%20stones%2C%20beads%20and%20seashells%20in%20her%20mosaic%20art.%20Initially%2C%20she%20acquired%20sample%20tiles%20from%20shops.%20Her%20friends%20who%20knew%20of%20her%20work%20saved%20up%20their%20broken%20pieces%20of%20crockery%20and%20tiles%20remaining%20from%20renovation%20work%20for%20her.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20as%20the%20business%20has%20grown%2C%20she%20purchases%20broken%20tiles%20in%20bulk%20from%20sellers.%20In%20cases%20where%20the%20client%20wants%20a%20particular%20colour%20or%20design%20she%20buys%20tiles%20from%20stores.%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAnother%20interesting%20raw%20material%20that%20she%20uses%20are%20the%20buoys%20in%20the%20sea.%20Made%20from%20fibre%20which%20is%20anti-corrosive%2C%20these%20buoys%C2%A0are%20being%20replaced%20by%20plastic%20ones%20these%20days%20by%20fishermen%20and%20are%20being%20discarded%20carelessly.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENaomi%20and%20Yohann%20then%20buy%20them%20from%20the%20fishermen%20to%20make%20planters%20embellished%20with%20mosaic%20or%20to%20build%20lotus%20ponds%20in%20which%20you%20can%20also%20put%20fish.%20The%20fibre%20is%20cleaned%2C%20refurbished%20and%20reused%20to%20make%20the%20signature%20planters%20or%20pond%20structures.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20adhere%20to%20our%20eco-friendly%20practices%20of%20minimum%20usage%20of%20chemicals%20on%20the%20wood.%20This%20way%2C%20it%20retains%20its%20natural%20beauty%20as%20well.%20We%20use%20linseed%20oil%20and%20tung%20oil%20as%20curing%20agents%20for%20protecting%20the%20wood%20and%20giving%20it%20a%20finish.%20However%2C%20we%20have%20to%20use%20an%20anti-termite%20solution%20to%20ensure%20the%20products%20are%20long-lasting.%20Otherwise%2C%20there%20is%20no%20point%20talking%20of%20sustainability%20if%20the%20products%20won%E2%80%99t%20last%20for%20the%20customer.%20We%20use%20machines%20to%20cut%20the%20wood%20but%20our%20products%20are%20hand%20polished%2C%E2%80%9D%20elaborates%20Yohann.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20wastage%20in%20the%20studio%20is%20kept%20to%20a%20minimum.%20Naomi%20collects%20the%20pieces%20that%20are%20left%20over%20from%20her%20pieces%20in%20three%20containers%20depending%20on%20their%20size%20and%20reuses%20them.%20Only%20the%20fine%20tile%20powder%20is%20wasted.%20Even%20in%20wood%20materials%2C%20wastage%20is%20avoided.%20For%20instance%2C%20a%20big%20piece%20of%20driftwood%20is%20cut%20into%20two%20so%20that%20one%20piece%20can%20be%20used%20to%20make%20a%20lamp%20and%20the%20other%20a%20side%20table.%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20458px)%20100vw%2C%20458px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FHer-fathers-bench-which-she-beautified_11zon-1697535543.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22458%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Naomi's%20father's%20bench%20which%20she%20beautified%20using%20broken%20mosaic%20tiles.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FHer-fathers-bench-which-she-beautified_11zon-1697535543.jpg%20458w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FHer-fathers-bench-which-she-beautified_11zon-1697535543-300x225.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FHer-fathers-bench-which-she-beautified_11zon-1697535543-150x113.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-332388%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22344%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3ENaomi%E2%80%99s%20father%E2%80%99s%20bench%20which%20she%20beautified%20using%20broken%20mosaic%20tiles.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%20%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EChanging%20perceptions%3C%2Fh2%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhen%20they%20hear%20the%20word%20mosaic%20in%20India%2C%20most%20people%20think%20of%20tiling%20chips%20put%20as%20flooring%20in%20rooms%2C%20terraces%20and%20on%20compound%20walls.%20Very%20few%20know%20that%20mosaic%20is%20a%20truly%20ancient%20art%20form%20which%20goes%20back%20to%20the%20ancient%20Mesopotamia%2C%20Greece%20and%20Rome%2C%20says%20Naomi.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20tried%20to%20give%20mosaic%20art%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F167841%2Fassam-riots-bengali-bhupen-hazarika-peace-story%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20recognition%20it%20deserves%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20am%20happy%20to%20say%20that%20my%20art%20is%20now%20being%20used%20indoors%20as%20wall%20art%2C%20murals%2C%20and%20picture%20frames%20replacing%20traditional%20paintings%2C%20and%20on%20table%20tops%20and%20cabinets%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20the%20elated%20artist.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESince%20they%20are%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F173413%2Fprayagraj-kumbh-2019-street-art-india%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eexclusive%20pieces%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20mosaic%20and%20wood%20art%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20come%20cheap.%20Also%2C%20since%20only%20the%20two%20of%20them%20handle%20the%20creative%20aspect%20of%20the%20business%2C%20they%20cannot%20make%20products%20in%20large%20numbers.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20there%20are%20two%20other%20people%20in%20their%20workshop%20who%20help%20with%20the%20mosaic%20works%20along%20with%20three%20freelancing%20carpenters%20and%20polishers%20for%20the%20woodwork.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20wall%20arts%20from%20their%20studio%20start%20at%20Rs%202%2C000-2%2C500%20per%20square%20foot%2C%20depending%20on%20the%20intricacy%20of%20design.%20The%20price%20of%20a%20driftwood%20centre%20table%20ranges%20from%20Rs%2018%2C000%20to%20Rs%2040%2C000%20which%20depends%20on%20the%20size%20and%20the%20quality%20of%20wood.%20Mosaic%20garden%20tables%2C%20two%20feet%20in%20diameter%2C%20cost%20Rs%2012%2C500.%20Floor%20lamps%20are%20priced%20at%20Rs%207%2C000-10%2C000.%20Planters%20range%20from%20Rs%205%2C000-15%2C000%2C%20depending%20on%20size.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EYohann%20has%20a%20residence-cum-studio%20in%20Bandra%20where%20clients%20can%20take%20a%20look%20at%20the%20products.%20The%20company%20gets%20orders%20from%20across%20India.%20%E2%80%9CIn%20fact%2C%20more%20than%20half%20of%20our%20clientele%20is%20outside%20Mumbai.%20Our%20products%20are%20large%20and%20meant%20for%20large%20spaces.%20Around%2060%20percent%20of%20our%20pieces%20are%20custom-made%20while%2040%20percent%20is%20from%20an%20inventory.%20We%20are%20now%20looking%20to%20grow%20the%20business%20through%20projects%20to%20do%20up%20villas%20and%20homes%20by%20collaborating%20with%20interior%20designers%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20537px)%20100vw%2C%20537px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FDriftwood-side-table_11zon-1697535566.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22537%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20side-table%20made%20with%20using%20a%20piece%20of%20driftwood.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FDriftwood-side-table_11zon-1697535566.jpg%20537w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FDriftwood-side-table_11zon-1697535566-262x300.jpg%20262w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FDriftwood-side-table_11zon-1697535566-500x572.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FDriftwood-side-table_11zon-1697535566-150x172.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-332390%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22614%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EA%20side-table%20made%20with%20using%20a%20piece%20of%20driftwood.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%20%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3ECreating%20unique%20products%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20their%20mosaic%20pieces%20are%20indeed%20eye-catching%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20their%20driftwood%20tables%20and%20other%20wares%20that%20are%20equally%20beautiful%20too.%20Driftwood%20is%20basically%20the%20wood%20that%20has%20been%20washed%20ashore%20onto%20a%20beach%20from%20the%20sea%2C%20lake%20or%20a%20river.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CDriftwood%20as%20well%20as%20upcycled%20wood%20come%20with%20a%20history.%20The%20character%2C%20texture%2C%20grain%2C%20and%20shape%20work%20as%20an%20inspiration%20for%20us.%20It%20requires%20a%20keen%20eye%2C%20and%20an%20active%20imagination%20to%20visualise%20and%20conceptualise%20the%20potential%20of%20every%20piece.%20And%20each%20one%20is%20different.%20Some%20make%20great%20lamps%2C%20some%20ingenious%20tabletops%2C%20some%20rustic%20benches.%20They%20can%20be%20used%20within%20the%20home%20and%20outdoors%20too.%C2%A0No%20two%20pieces%20are%20the%20same%20and%20the%20challenge%20is%20always%20to%20create%20something%20different.%20It%20is%20the%20joy%20and%20immense%20satisfaction%20of%20creating%20art%20from%20waste%20that%20drives%20us%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Naomi.%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDriftwood%20has%20to%20undergo%20a%20rigorous%20process%20before%20it%20can%20be%20worked%20with.%20It%20involves%20scrubbing%20and%20cleaning%20the%20piece%2C%20bleaching%20it%20over%20a%20period%20of%20weeks%20to%20remove%20the%20insects%20as%20well%20as%20lighten%20the%20wood%C2%A0tones.%20Then%20it%20is%20protected%20from%20termites%20and%20kept%20out%20in%20the%20sun%20to%20dry%20thoroughly%2C%20she%20explains.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CMy%20entire%20day%20is%20spent%20in%20my%20workshop%2C%20especially%20if%20we%20have%20hard%20deadlines.%20At%20times%2C%20day%20creeps%20into%20night.%20Sometimes%2C%20I%20even%20forget%20to%20eat.%20I%20hire%20more%20hands%20on%20a%20daily%20wage%20basis%20if%20I%20need%20extra%20assistance.%20While%20I%20lay%20the%20creative%20groundwork%20for%20a%20piece%2C%20the%20machine%20work%20is%20handled%20by%20my%20team%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.